result.execSummary:
All charges against Alaquay Daisy Templeton in this case have been dismissed. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Alaquay Daisy Templeton is presumed innocent.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 09:42 AM Defendant Alaquay Daisy Templeton in court with attorney Lindsay L Erickson.  Alexander Paul Seifert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Alaquay Daisy Templeton appeared by video means with Attorney. Erickson and Templeton appear via Zoom. Court calls 20CT56 and 22CM03. Erickson states that she sent a letter to the defendant but has not heard from her, verified address. Templeton states that she has tried to contact Erickson. Erickson states she had no messages on her phone, asks Court to read charges and penalties. Court states it has already. Erickson waives reading on both complaints, enters NG pleas to all counts on each complaint, set for JT. Court verifies address and phone number.
Adjourned initial appearance on March 30, 2022 at 09:45 am.

10:31 AM Defendant Alaquay Daisy Templeton in court.  Alexander Paul Seifert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Alaquay Daisy Templeton appeared by video means. Court calls 20CT56 and 22CM3. Templeton states that the Court appoints Lindsay Erickson, not sure why she is not here today, Templeton just received the information as to who was appointed on Friday. Court will set both matters for another AIA, no more Zoom appearances, continues bond on both, sets for AIA on 3/30/22 at 9:45 AM.

records.addlTxt: Adjourned initial appearance on March 16, 2022 at 10:30 am.

10:31 AM Defendant Alaquay Daisy Templeton in court.  Alexander Paul Seifert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Alaquay Daisy Templeton appeared by video means. Court calls 22CM03 and 20CT56. Templeton states that she does not qualify for SPD and was send a "dean appointment" form by SPD. Court will allow another adjournment, continues bond on both matters, must have court appointed attorney form filled in completely and send to COC Office prior to her next court date. Court sets both matters set for AIA on 3/16/22 at 10:30 AM, mail in form today or drop off at COC Office.
Adjourned initial appearance on February 9, 2022 at 10:30 am.

09:14 AM Defendant Alaquay Daisy Templeton in court.  Alexander Paul Seifert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Alaquay Daisy Templeton appeared by video means. All other parties appear in person. Court calls 20CT56 and 22CM03. Templeton states she does not have the complaint for 22CM03. State will send one. Court reads charges and penalties and right to attorney and court appointed attorney on 22CM03. Templeton understands charges and penalties, would like SPD - does not have finances to her own. Court refers to SPD and keep contacting them until she hears from them - set this matter for AIA on 2/9/22 at 10:30 AM. Court - 20CT56 - asks why she did not appear in August of 2020 and September of 2020 and May of 2021 - looks like bond is posted in the wrong case - move the $700.00 bond from 22CM03 to 22CT56. Templeton explains her missing Court (had Michigan address). Court sets bond on 20CT56 at $700.00 cash that is already posted off the warrant - will send the bond and a condition of the bond is to sign and return it to COC Office within 10 days and no consumption of alcohol, also refers to SPD on this case, set bond on 22CM03 at $1,000.00 signature bond, no consumption of alcohol and must sign and return to COC Office within 10 days, sets this case for AIA on 2/9/22 at 10:30 AM, reminds her to contact SPD. Court confirms address and phone number.
